StrikeIron provides a cloud-based Data Quality Suite including email verification, address verification, phone validation, phone append, and sales tax calculation solutions. The company is based in Research Triangle Park, N.C. It was founded by Bob Brauer (founder of DataFlux), Richard Holcomb (co-founder of HAHT Software and Q+E Software), and Robert Dale in 2003. StrikeIron is a leader in Data-as-a-Service with its delivery platform IronCloud.
To date the company has raised over $16 million USD in venture funding. It is financially backed by Ascent Ventures, The Aurora Funds, and NC IDEA.
The current CEO of the company is Sean O'Leary.
